p: Native species growth differed among non-native pairings ( F 4,657 = 10.95, P < 0.01). Natives had the greatest biomass with S. altissimum and the least with B. tectorum. Non-native species growth similarly differed among native pairings ( F 3,657 = 4.48, P < 0.01). Non-natives had the greatest aboveground biomass with L. sericeus and the least with K. macrantha.
